-- Two Held in London Terrorism Investigation, Police Say
-- B y   J e r e m y   H o d g e s
-- 2012-06-28T15:44:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-28/two-held-in-london-terrorism-investigation-police-say.html
U.K. police arrested two men ages
18 and 32 as part of an anti-terrorism investigation.  Both men, arrested today at different East  London 
addresses, were being held at a central London police station.  They were arrested on suspicion of “the commission,
preparation or instigation of acts of terrorism,” the London
Metropolitan Police said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeremy Hodges in London
at   jhodges17@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anthony Aarons at   aaarons@bloomberg.net . 